ing%20thing%20to%20see.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Crew-7%20is%20a%20shining%20example%20of%20the%20power%20of%20both%20American%20ingenuity%20and%20what%20we%20can%20accomplish%20when%20we%20work%20together.%20Aboard%20the%20station%2C%20the%20crew%20will%20conduct%20more%20than%20200%20science%20experiments%20and%20technology%20demonstrations%20to%20prepare%20for%20missions%20to%20the%20Moon%2C%20Mars%2C%20and%20beyond%2C%20all%20while%20benefitting%20humanity%20on%20Earth.%20By%20partnering%20with%20countries%20around%20the%20world%2C%20NASA%20is%20engaging%20the%20best%20scientific%20minds%20to%20enable%20our%20bold%20missions%2C%20and%20it's%20clear%20that%20we%20can%20do%20more%20%E2%80%93%20and%20we%20can%20learn%20more%20%E2%80%93%20when%20we%20work%20together%2C''%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fpress-release%2Fnasa-s-spacex-crew-7-launches-to-international-space-station%5C%22%3ENASA%20Administrator%20Bill%20Nelson.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20the%20Astronauts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Ms.%20Moghbeli's%20first%20trip%20into%20space%20since%20her%20selection%20as%20a%20NASA%20astronaut%20in%202017.%C2%A0As%20mission%20commander%2C%20she%20is%20responsible%20for%20all%20phases%20of%20flight%2C%20from%20launch%20to%20re-entry.%20She%20will%20serve%20as%20an%20Expedition%2069%2F70%20flight%20engineer%20aboard%20the%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Mogensen%20from%20Copenhagen%20was%20selected%20as%20an%20ESA%20astronaut%20in%202009%20and%20became%20the%20first%20Danish%20citizen%20in%20space%20after%20launching%20aboard%20a%20Soyuz%20for%20a%2010-day%20mission%20to%20the%20space%20station%20in%202015.%20He%20has%20since%20served%20as%20a%20crew%20member%20for%20NASA%20Extreme%20Environment%20Mission%20Operations%20undersea%20missions%2017%20and%2019.%20As%20the%20pilot%20on%20Crew-7%2C%20he%20is%20responsible%20for%20spacecraft%20systems%20and%20performance%20aboard%20the%20station%2C%20he%20will%20serve%20as%20an%20Expedition%2069%20flight%20engineer%20and%20Expedition%2070%20commander.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Furukawa%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20making%20his%20second%20trip%20to%20space%2C%20having%20spent%20165%20days%20aboard%20the%20space%20station%20as%20part%20of%20Expeditions%2028%20and%2029%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20Mr%20Borisov%20is%20making%20his%20first%20trip%20to%20space%20and%20will%20serve%20as%20a%20mission%20specialist%2C%20working%20to%20monitor%20the%20spacecraft%20during%20the%20dynamic%20launch%20and%20entry%20phases%20of%20flight.%20He%20entered%20the%20Roscosmos%20Cosmonaut%20Corps%20as%20a%20test%20cosmonaut%20candidate%20in%202018%20and%20will%20serve%20as%20a%20flight%20engineer%20for%20Expedition%2069%2F70.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693108080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fbr37jreo_nasas-crew7-mission_625x300_27_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-nasas-crew-7-mission-launches-4-astronauts-from-4-countries-to-space-station-4333037%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Crew-7%20mission%20is%20commanded%20by%20Jasmin%20Moghbeli%20from%20the%20USA%2C%20Andreas%20Mogensen%20from%20Denmark%2C%20Satoshi%20Furukawa%20from%20Japan%2C%20and%20Konstantin%20Borisov%20from%20Russia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-nasas-crew-7-mission-launches-4-astronauts-from-4-countries-to-space-station-4333037%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-nasas-crew-7-mission-launches-4-astronauts-from-4-countries-to-space-station-4333037%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-nasas-crew-7-mission-launches-4-astronauts-from-4-countries-to-space-station-4333037%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22H