20200407_4.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Shinzo%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20first%20priority%20in%20office%20was%20to%20rebuild%20the%20economy.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20national%20budget%20is%20larger%20than%20the%20GDP%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20or%20Turkey.%20However%2C%2070%20per%20cent%20of%20it%20disappears%20in%20just%20three%20areas%20of%20expenditure%3A%20redemption%20of%20government%20bonds%20and%20related%20interest%20payments%3B%20subsidies%20to%20local%20governments%3B%20and%20social%20security%20expenditure%2C%20mainly%20on%20healthcare%20for%20the%20elderly.%20For%20long-term%20growth%2C%20more%20money%20must%20be%20spent%20on%20basic%20science%20research%20and%20education%2C%20but%20as%20long%20as%20the%20overall%20pie%20does%20not%20grow%E2%80%94that%20is%20to%20say%2C%20as%20long%20as%20economic%20growth%20cannot%20be%20achieved%E2%80%94money%20could%20not%20be%20spent%20on%20anything%20future-oriented%2C%20be%20it%20education%20or%20defence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbe%E2%80%99s%20well-known%20economic%20policy%2C%20termed%20%E2%80%98Abenomics%E2%80%99%2C%20started%20as%20a%20short-term%20demand%20stimulus%20and%20then%20began%20to%20try%20a%20series%20of%20measures%20to%20help%20the%20economy%20grow.%20This%20policy%20can%20be%20termed%20a%20success.%20Before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit%20Japan%20and%20the%20world%2C%20Japan%20could%20achieve%20full%20employment%3A%20ninety-eight%20out%20of%20100%20university%20students%20could%20find%20jobs%20upon%20graduation.%20The%20same%20figure%20applied%20even%20for%20those%20looking%20for%20employment%20after%20finishing%20high%20school%2C%20with%2098%20per%20cent%20of%20such%20individuals%20finding%20stable%20work.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20bursting%20of%20the%20speculative%20bubble%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20young%20people%20in%20Japan%20were%20allowed%20to%20believe%20that%20there%20would%20be%20hope%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20email%20illustrated%20the%20fact%20that%20young%20people%20took%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20message%20to%20heart.%20The%20economy%20is%20based%20on%20human%20activity%20and%20people%20change%20their%20behaviour%20depending%20on%20whether%20they%20are%20optimistic%20or%20pessimistic%20about%20the%20future.%20Whether%20in%20Japan%20or%20India%2C%20there%20are%20only%20three%20paths%20through%20which%20an%20economy%20can%20grow%3A%20increase%20in%20labour%20input%2C%20increase%20of%20capital%20stock%20or%20increase%20of%20total%20factor%20productivity.%C2%A0%20That%20much%20is%20in%20every%20economics%20textbook.%20What%20no%20textbook%20touches%20on%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20none%20of%20these%20factors%20could%20be%20increased%20without%20people%2C%20especially%20entrepreneurs%2C%20having%20hope%20for%20the%20future.%20Unless%20people%20believe%20that%20the%20future%20will%20be%20better%20than%20the%20present%2C%20nothing%20positive%20will%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20341px)%2085vw%2C%20341px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171543%2F01.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22341%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171543%2F01.jpeg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171543%2F01-196x300.jpeg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171543%2F01-667x1024.jpeg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670011%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22524%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESanjaya%20Baru%20(Edited)%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Importance%20of%20Shinzo%20Abe%3A%20India%2C%20Japan%20and%20the%20Indo-Pacific%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHarperCollins%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20economies%20where%20hope%20is%20a%20rare%20commodity%20are%20so%20rare%20that%20standard%20economics%20textbooks%20dare%20not%20mention%20the%20importance%20of%20hope.%20Japan%20was%20that%20rare%20exception%3A%20the%20economy%20where%20hope%20was%20the%20rarest%20of%20all%20scarce%20commodities.%20It%20was%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20eagerness%20to%20give%20young%20people%20hope%20for%20the%20future%20that%20led%20him%20to%20do%20all%20he%20could%20to%20attract%20first%20the%20Olympic%20Games%20and%20later%20the%20World%20Expo%E2%80%94which%20is%20to%20be%20held%20in%202025%20at%20Osaka.%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20achievements%20in%20economic%20policy%20was%20to%20give%20hope%20to%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20problems%20plaguing%20the%20country%20are%20the%20dwindling%20number%20of%20children%20and%20an%20ageing%20population.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20easy%20problem%20to%20solve.%20There%20are%20no%20textbooks%20to%20consult%20to%20help%20tackle%20this%20issue.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20solution%20may%20well%20set%20the%20first%20such%20precedent%20in%20human%20history.%C2%A0%20What%20is%20certain%20is%20that%20nothing%20will%20be%20resolved%20unless%20people%20have%20hope%20for%20the%20future.%20And%20for%20the%20Japanese%20people%20to%20have%20confidence%20in%20their%20country%E2%80%99s%20future%2C%20stability%20in%20the%20external%20environment%20is%20essential.%20Fewer%20people%20would%20invest%20in%20Japan%E2%80%94and%20fewer%20children%20would%20be%20born%E2%80%94if%20they%20think%20the%20country%20might%20become%20dependent%20on%20China%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20for%20Abe%20therefore%20were%20firstly%20to%20grow%20the%20economy%2C%20secondly%20to%20use%20the%20fruits%20of%20that%20growth%20to%20constantly%20improve%20defence%20capabilities%20and%20thirdly%20to%20expand%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20space%20and%20neutralize%20Chinese%20coercive%20activities%20by%20strengthening%20relations%20with%20India%20and%20Australia%20in%20addition%20to%20its%20long-standing%20alliance%20partner%2C%20the%20US.%20These%20three%20challenges%20create%20a%20self-reinforcing%20causal%20loop%2C%20both%20positively%20and%20negatively.%20Prime%20Minister%20Abe%20was%20keenly%20aware%20of%20this%20dynamic.%20Foreign%20investors%20visiting%20Tokyo%20advised%20the%20actors%20in%20his%20administration%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20economy%20rather%20than%20security.%20But%20for%20Abe%2C%20the%20economy%20and%20security%20were%20as%20inseparable%20as%20his%20own%20vitality%20and%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Abe%20first%20met%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20had%20just%20won%20the%20US%20presidential%20election%2C%20he%20persuaded%20him%20to%20see%20that%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20to%20the%20US%E2%80%93Japan%20alliance%20was%20not%20North%20Korea%2C%20but%20China.%20Tokyo%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20confront%20the%20Chinese%20threat%20can%20only%20be%20achieved%20through%20overcoming%20all%20three%20of%20the%20challenges%20mentioned%20in%20the%20previous%20paragraph%3A%20it%20must%20strengthen%20its%20economy%2C%20build%20up%20its%20military%20and%20make%20its%20cooperation%20with%20Australia%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%20as%20strong%20as%20possible.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20Abe%20saved%20the%20Trans-Pacific%20Partnership%20(TPP)%20from%20the%20brink%20of%20oblivion%20and%20brought%20it%20to%20fruition.%20He%20also%20succeeded%20in%20forging%20the%20EU%E2%80%93Japan%20Economic%20Partnership%20Agreement%20(EPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Abe%2C%20Japan%20became%20the%20standard-bearer%20for%20a%20free%2C%20open%20and%20rules-based%20international%20economic%20order%2C%20which%20was%20unparalleled%20in%20the%20150%20years%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20modern%20history.%20He%20developed%20the%20arguments%20he%20made%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20in%202007%20to%20create%20QUAD.%20The%20US%E2%80%93Japan%20alliance%20has%20grown%20stronger%20than%20ever%20through%20the%20administrations%20of%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20and%20the%20Australia%E2%80%93Japan%20relationship%20has%20grown%20to%20become%20a%20quasi-alliance.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20space%20has%20expanded%20markedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%20has%20a%20constitution%20that%20is%20unique%20in%20the%20world.%20Article%209%2C%20paragraph%201%2C%20states%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20Japanese%20people%20forever%20renounce%20war%20as%20a%20sovereign%20right%20of%20the%20nation%20and%20the%20threat%20or%20use%20of%20force%20as%20means%20of%20settling%20international%20disputes%E2%80%99.%20This%20builds%20on%20the%20trend%20of%20outlawing%20war%20since%20World%20War%20I%20and%20is%20not%20a%20factor%20unique%20to%20the%20Japanese%20Constitution.%20What%20remains%20unique%20today%20is%20that%20the%20subsequent%20paragraph%202%20states%3A%20%E2%80%98In%20order%20to%20accomplish%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20preceding%20paragraph%2C%20land%2C%20sea%20and%20air%20forces%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20war%20potential%2C%20will%20never%20be%20maintained.%20The%20right%20of%20belligerency%20of%20the%20state%20will%20not%20be%20recognized.%E2%80%99%20Because%20of%20this%20section%2C%20many%20Japanese%20constitutional%20scholars%20still%20regard%20the%20Japanese%20Self-Defence%20Forces%20(SDF)%20as%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20constitution.%20This%20is%20also%20the%20reason%20why%20the%20SDF%20is%20not%20referred%20to%20as%20an%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20actions%20have%20been%20constrained%20by%20the%20limited%20interpretations%20of%20its%20constitution%2C%20which%20state%20that%20the%20SDF%20%E2%80%98may%20not%20return%20fire%2C%20whether%20by%20missiles%20or%20artillery%20shells%2C%20unless%20it%20is%20hit%20by%20the%20first%20shot%E2%80%99%20and%20that%20%E2%80%98whatever%20friendly%20forces%20are%20attacked%2C%20it%20may%20not%20join%20in%20and%20return%20fire%20unless%20it%20is%20attacked%20itself%E2%80%99.%20Under%20this%20interpretation%2C%20in%20the%20hypothetical%20situation%20of%20Taiwan%20coming%20under%20attack%20by%20China%2C%20the%20Japanese%20forces%20in%20the%20immediate%20vicinity%20will%20be%20unable%20to%20do%20anything%20about%20it%20even%20if%20their%20allies%20such%20as%20the%20US%20suffer%20military%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20357px)%2085vw%2C%20357px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171744%2FDr-e1617591669604.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22357%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171744%2FDr-e1617591669604.jpeg%20903w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171744%2FDr-e1617591669604-226x300.jpeg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26171744%2FDr-e1617591669604-771x1024.jpeg%20771w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670012%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22475%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETomohiko%20Taniguchi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbe%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20have%20led%20to%20Japan%20receiving%20147%20F-35%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20jets%20from%20the%20US.%20But%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20superior%20planes%20Japan%20has%2C%20they%20are%20simply%20useless%20as%20long%20as%20the%20interpretation%20of%20its%20constitution%20remains%20unchanged.%C2%A0%20If%20over%20a%20hundred%20Japanese%20fighter%20jets%20remain%20grounded%20despite%20Chinese%20aircraft%20attacking%20US%20forces%2C%20the%20US%E2%80%93Japan%20alliance%20will%20at%20once%20lose%20its%20significance.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20security%20environment%20would%20deteriorate%20instantly%20and%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Abe%20succeeded%20in%20passing%20a%20series%20of%20legislative%20bills%2C%20the%20enactment%20of%20which%20changed%20this%20narrow%20interpretation%20of%20the%20constitution.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20military%20attack%20by%20China%20on%20Taiwan%2C%20the%20SDF%20facilities%20on%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20westernmost%20island%20(Yonaguni%20Island)%20would%20not%20be%20unharmed.%20The%20US%20military%20would%20respond%20by%20mobilizing%20from%20bases%20in%20Japan%20to%20defend%20Taiwan.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%20of%20imminent%20and%20existential%20threat%20to%20Japan%2C%20the%20Japanese%20Self-Defence%20Forces%20and%20the%20US%20military%20would%20be%20able%20to%20collectively%20exercise%20their%20right%20to%20self-defence.%20Abe%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20political%20capital%20to%20pass%20the%20bills%20that%20made%20this%20possible.%20Now%2C%20protection%20of%20US%20military%20assets%20are%20a%20regular%20obligation%20for%20the%20SDF%2C%20and%20US%20military%20vessels%20and%20aircraft%20operate%20under%20ever-present%20SDF%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20accomplishments%20in%20economic%20revitalization%20and%20strengthening%20of%20deterrence%20as%20a%20backdrop%2C%20Abe%20faced%20Xi%20Jinping%20of%20China.%20The%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20is%20an%20organisation%20that%20believes%20in%20power%2C%20and%20power%20alone%2C%20and%20Xi%20is%20the%20embodiment%20of%20such%20a%20party.%20However%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20power%20was%20enhanced%20by%20Mr%20Abe%2C%20Xi%20began%20to%20pay%20more%20heed%20to%20Tokyo.%20Nowadays%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98One%20Belt%2C%20One%20Road%E2%80%99%20does%20not%20appear%20in%20the%20global%20discourse%20as%20much%20as%20it%20used%20to.%20When%20Abe%20fell%20to%20the%20bullets%20of%20fanatics%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20sent%20his%20condolences.%20The%20use%20of%20the%20first%20person%20in%20the%20condolence%20message%20was%20unusual%20for%20a%20Chinese%20leader.%20Even%20Xi%20must%20have%20felt%20that%20he%20and%20Abe%20had%20a%20kind%20of%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20using%20his%20varied%20diplomatic%20skills%2C%20Abe%20attempted%20to%20conclude%20a%20peace%20treaty%20with%20the%20President%20of%20Russia%2C%20Vladimir%20Putin.%20He%20met%20with%20Putin%20twenty-seven%20times%20and%20was%20prepared%20to%20make%20some%20compromises%20to%20achieve%20his%20one%20objective%3A%20to%20reduce%20the%20military%20threat%20to%20the%20north%20of%20Japan%20by%20bringing%20military%20tensions%20with%20Russia%20under%20control.%20This%20would%20enable%20him%20to%20concentrate%20any%20spare%20SDF%20capacity%20entirely%20on%20the%20southwestern%20part%20of%20Japan%20to%20defend%20against%20China.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20It%20was%20a%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politik%3C%2Fem%3E%20oriented%20diplomacy%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20bear%20any%20fruit.%20Ironically%2C%20Putin%20was%20not%20a%20dictator%20who%20could%20change%20relations%20with%20Japan%20by%20a%20single%20decision.%20Japan%20imposed%20harsh%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20following%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20now%20relations%20between%20Russia%20and%20Japan%20are%20even%20worse%20than%20they%20were%20before%20Abe%20began%20talks%20with%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20North%20Korea%20and%20China%20are%20vertically%20aligned%20across%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan%20and%20all%20three%20share%20borders%20with%20Japanese%20territory.%20None%20of%20these%20countries%20has%20ever%20experienced%20anything%20akin%20to%20open%20democracy%2C%20and%20all%20three%20believe%20in%20the%20power%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%3A%20in%20fact%2C%20they%20are%20increasing%20their%20respective%20arsenals%20of%20warheads.%20This%20means%20that%20no%20G7%20country%20is%20in%20a%20more%20dangerous%20location%20than%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%20needed%20allies.%20No%20matter%20how%20strong%20the%20economy%20is%20and%20how%20energized%20the%20people%20are%2C%20Japan%20can%20be%20weak%20in%20the%20long%20term%20if%20the%20external%20environment%20is%20so%20dangerous.%20Japan%20had%20to%20be%20able%20to%20state%20with%20confidence%E2%80%94both%20domestically%20and%20internationally%E2%80%94that%20it%20is%20not%20alone%2C%20that%20it%20has%20partners%20and%20allies.%20It%20needed%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20whole%20world%20could%20understand%E2%80%94one%20that%20respects%20freedom%2C%20human%20rights%2C%20democracy%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%E2%80%94and%20to%20declare%20it%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECreating%20a%20new%20geographical%20concept%20and%20spreading%20it%20around%20the%20world%20is%20no%20mean%20feat.%20It%20was%20Shinzo%20Abe%20who%20pursued%20this%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20in%20Delhi%2C%20in%20the%20Australian%20Parliament%20in%20Canberra%20and%20in%20the%20US%20Congress%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20It%20is%20also%20to%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20credit%20that%20he%20launched%20QUAD%20and%20fostered%20cooperation%20between%20Australia%2C%20India%2C%20Japan%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20these%20diplomatic%20efforts%20have%20reassured%20Japan%20and%20the%20Japanese%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20Abe%20first%20came%20to%20power%20in%202006%2C%20he%20realized%20that%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20concept%20had%20become%20outdated.%20He%20felt%20that%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20a%20larger%20concept%20that%20would%20balance%20China%E2%80%99s%20intimidation%20as%20well%20as%20a%20framework%20that%20would%20encompass%20and%20emphasize%20fast-growing%20India%20as%20one%20pole%2C%20both%20politically%20and%20economically.%20Thus%2C%20what%20Abe%20created%E2%80%94and%20the%20world%20accepted%E2%80%94was%20Free%20and%20Open%20Indo-Pacific%20(Free%20and%20Open%20Indo-Pacific)%20and%20the%20Quadrilateral%20Security%20Dialogue%20(QUAD).%20Under%20Abe%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%20modern%20history%20Japan%20succeeded%20%C2%A0in%20launching%20a%20new%20concept%20that%20has%20defined%20the%20world%20discourse.%20Abe%E2%80%99s%20success%20as%20a%20politician%20is%20unprecedented%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETomohiko%20Taniguchi%20is%20former%20special%20aide%20and%20speechwriter%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Shinzo%20Abe.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExtracted%20with%20permission%20from%20Sanjaya%20Baru%20(Edited)%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Importance%20of%20Shinzo%20Abe%3A%20India%2C%20Japan%20and%20the%20Indo-Pacific%3Cem%3E%2C%20HarperCollins%2C%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693101605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26172107%2FShinzo_Abe_20200407_4.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fshinzo-abes-new-japan-in-a-new-asia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Under%20Abe%2C%20Japan%20became%20the%20standard-bearer%20for%20a%20free%2C%20open%20and%20rules-based%20international%20economic%20order%2C%20which%20was%20unparalleled%20in%20the%20150%20years%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20modern%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fshinzo-abes-new-japan-in-a-new-asia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%229%2F11%20Victims'%20Families%20Split%20Over%20Proposal%20to%20Spare%20Suspects'%20Lives%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20proposal%20to%20allow%20alleged%20perpetrators%20of%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%20to%20plead%20guilty%20and%20avoid%20the%20death%20penalty%20poses%20a%20powerful%20dilemma%20for%20victims'%20families%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20still%20want%20to%20seek%20the%20ultimate%20retribution%20after%20two%20decades%20of%20legal%20limbo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20detailed%20by%20prosecutors%20in%20a%20letter%20this%20month%20could%20offer%20families%20of%20the%20nearly%203%2C000%20victims%20the%20best%20path%20to%20a%20resolution%20of%20a%20case%20bogged%20down%20in%20pre-trial%20maneuverings%20in%20the%20Guantanamo%20military%20commissions%20for%20years%20--%20and%20with%20no%20end%20in%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20families%20of%20those%20killed%20in%20New%20York's%20World%20Trade%20Center%2C%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20and%20in%20Pennsylvania%20say%20a%20deal%20without%20a%20trial%20could%20mean%20the%20entire%20truth%20about%20what%20happened%20on%20September%2011%2C%202001%20might%20never%20be%20told.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20say%20that%20every%20year%20of%20delay%20means%20that%20more%20people%20pass%20away%20without%20seeing%20justice%20for%20their%20slain%20relatives%20--%20and%20increases%20the%20risk%20that%20the%20aging%20defendants%20themselves%20could%20die%20without%20ever%20being%20found%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%209%2F11%20family%20members%20want%20justice%20and%20accountability.%20Too%20many%20of%20us%20have%20died%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20without%20either%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20September%2011th%20Families%20for%20Peaceful%20Tomorrows%2C%20which%20backs%20the%20plea%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlea%20agreements%2C%20which%20could%20be%20made%20right%20now%2C%20would%20offer%20finality%3A%20an%20end%20to%20the%209%2F11%20military%20commission%2C%20clear%20admissions%20of%20guilt%2C%20and%20life%20sentences%20without%20parole%20or%20any%20possibility%20of%20appeal%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Dennis%20McGinley%20of%20the%20group%209%2F11%20Justice%20said%20the%20deal%20would%20leave%20untold%20the%20full%20story%20behind%20the%20attack%20that%20killed%20his%20brother%20Danny%20in%20the%20south%20tower%20of%20the%20World%20Trade%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20this%20is%2C%20is...%20to%20prevent%20a%20trial%20from%20taking%20place%20where%20Khalid%20Sheikh%20Mohammed%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20spill%20the%20beans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20self-described%209%2F11%20mastermind%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BKSM.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvidence%20tainted%20by%20torture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%2C%20outlined%20in%20an%20August%201%20letter%20from%20the%20office%20of%20the%20chief%20prosecutor%20for%20the%20Pentagon-run%20military%20tribunals%2C%20has%20been%20in%20preparation%20for%20two%20years%20in%20the%20case%20of%20KSM%2C%20Ammar%20al-Baluchi%2C%20Walid%20bin%20Attash%2C%20Ramzi%20bin%20al-Shibh%20and%20Mustafa%20al-Hawsawi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20has%20been%20held%20for%20more%20than%2016%20years%20at%20the%20US%20naval%20base%20in%20Guantanamo%20Bay%2C%20Cuba%2C%20where%20they%20are%20among%20the%20last%2030%20of%20what%20was%20once%20nearly%20800%20people%20detained%20extrajudicially%20by%20the%20United%20States%20after%209%2F11.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20formally%20arraigned%20in%202012%20for%20the%20case%2C%20but%20since%20the%20beginning%20it%20has%20been%20mired%20in%20debates%20over%20prosecutors'%20intent%20to%20use%20evidence%20that%20defense%20attorneys%20say%20was%20extracted%20through%20systematic%20torture%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20CIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20implicitly%20acknowledges%20that%20prosecutors%20cannot%20say%20when%20a%20full%20trial%20would%20begin%2C%20if%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20proposed%20deal%2C%20the%20accused%20%26quot%3Bwould%20accept%20criminal%20responsibility%20for%20their%20actions%20and%20plead%20guilty%20to%20the%20charged%20offenses%20in%20exchange%20for%20not%20receiving%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20the%20defendants%20would%20have%20to%20agree%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bstipulation%20of%20facts%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20provide%20details%20of%20the%20September%2011%20plot%20and%20their%20roles%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20prosecutors%20said%20no%20deal%20was%20finalized%2C%20the%20letter%20was%20confirmation%20that%20such%20an%20arrangement%20appears%20to%20be%20where%20the%20case%20is%20heading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20indeed%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20more%20delays%20sharpened%20last%20week%20when%20a%20military%20judge%20in%20a%20separate%20Guantanamo%20case%20rejected%20torture-tainted%20confessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFailed%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDropping%20the%20death%20penalty%20in%20the%20case%20though%20could%20spark%20an%20emotional%20backlash%20not%20only%20from%20victims'%20families%20but%20from%20Americans%20across%20the%20country%2C%20where%20anger%20remains%20deep%20over%20the%20Al-Qaeda%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKhalid%20Sheikh%20Mohammed%20and%20the%20other%209%2F11%20perpetrators%20should%20never%20be%20given%20a%20plea%20deal%20and%20should%20face%20the%20full%20measure%20of%20justice%20for%20their%20actions%20--%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20New%20York%20Congressman%20Mike%20Lawler%2C%20criticizing%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20for%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Terry%20Rockefeller%2C%20of%20the%20Peaceful%20Tomorrows%20group%2C%20said%20the%20deal%20is%20the%20best%20chance%20for%20families%20to%20get%20closure%2C%20with%20the%20certainty%20that%20defendants%20will%20have%20no%20ability%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERockefeller%2C%20whose%20sister%20died%20in%20the%20World%20Trade%20Center%2C%20said%20that%20in%20private%20meetings%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20prosecutors%20had%20no%20answer%20when%20asked%20how%20long%20a%20trial%20might%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20military%20commissions%20have%20by%20and%20large%20been%20a%20failed%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%20trial%20is%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20death%20penalty%20because%20of%20the%20torture%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcGinley%20said%20the%20type%20of%20punishment%20didn't%20matter%20to%20him%20at%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20it's%20the%20death%20penalty%20or%20life%20in%20prison%2C%20I%20want%20whatever%20the%20terrorists%20don't%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20argued%20that%20a%20settlement%20will%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20keep%20information%20classified%20about%20the%20attacks%20--%20information%20he%20said%20would%20implicate%20Saudi%20Arabia%20more%20deeply%20in%20the%20carnage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERiyadh%20has%20long%20denied%20any%20links%20with%20the%20hijackers%2C%20but%20suspicions%20have%20lingered%20over%20whether%20the%20attacks%20were%20funded%20with%20Saudi%20money%2C%20and%20McGinley's%20group%20alleges%20that%20Saudi%20agents%20were%20involved%20in%20various%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20thinks%20a%20trial%20-%20with%20all%20evidence%20declassified%20-%20would%20be%20the%20best%20chance%20for%20families%20to%20get%20justice%20after%20two%20decades%20of%20waiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%209%2F11%20community%20has%20been%20getting%20used%20and%20abused%20by%20our%20government%20for%20the%20last%2022%20years.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20it's%20almost%20cruel%20and%20unusual%20punishment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693101060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2018-09%2Fm3p30fq_twin-towers%2C9-11-attack_650_625x300_10_September_18.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F9-11-victims-families-split-over-proposal-to-spare-suspects-lives-4333005%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20proposal%20to%20allow%20alleged%20perpetrators%20of%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%20to%20plead%20guilty%20and%20avoid%20the%20death%20penalty%20poses%20a%20powerful%20dilemma%20for%20victims'%20families%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20still%20want%20to%20seek%20the%20ultimate%20retribution%20after%20two%20decades%20of%20legal%20limbo.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F9-11-victims-families-split-over-proposal-to-spare-suspects-lives-4333005%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F9-11-victims-families-split-over-proposal-to-spare-suspects-lives-4333005%2Famp%2