st%20gruesome%20hate%20crime%20murders%20in%20recent%20Texas%20history.%20(AP%20Photo%2FJuan%20Lozano)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cbc7095d2ce7811e1172035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222430%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMylinda%20Byrd%20Washington%2C%2066%2C%20right%2C%20and%20Louvon%20Byrd%20Harris%2C%2061%2C%20hold%20up%20photographs%20of%20their%20brother%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20Byrd%20Jr.%20was%20the%20victim%20of%20what%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20gruesome%20hate%20crime%20murders%20in%20recent%20Texas%20history.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJuan%20Lozano%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPeople%20in%20Jasper%20are%20in%20many%20ways%20still%20dealing%20with%20the%20aftermath%20of%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.'s%201998%20murder.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMany%20residents%20say%20the%20perpetrators%20were%20caught%2C%20but%20the%20crime%20still%20unfairly%20weighs%20on%20the%20town.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20Washington%20Post%20report%2C%20Byrd's%20family%20said%20that%20local%20officials%20want%20to%20move%20past%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%201998%2C%20the%20murder%20of%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20forever%20changed%20the%20small%20East%20Texas%20town%20of%20Jasper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BJewel%20of%20the%20Forest%2C%26quot%3B%20Jasper%20and%20its%20surrounding%20area%20had%20long%20been%20known%20for%20its%20natural%20beauty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20changed%20after%20Byrd%2C%20a%2049-year-old%20Black%20man%2C%20was%20chained%20to%20the%20back%20of%20a%20pickup%20truck%20by%20three%20white%20men%20and%20dragged%20by%20his%20ankles%20for%20more%20than%20two%20miles%20on%20a%20winding%20road%20outside%20of%20the%20city%20limits.%20During%20the%20shockingly%20brutal%20act%2C%20Byrd%20was%20decapitated%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20his%20battered%20body%20were%20discovered%20along%20the%20route%20his%20killers%20took%20that%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJasper%2C%20which%20was%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20more%20racially%20integrated%20areas%20of%20the%20region%2C%20sought%20to%20dispel%20the%20belief%20that%20their%20community%20was%20a%20hotbed%20of%20racism%20and%20unbridled%20hate.%20Similar%20to%20many%20of%20the%20racial%20reconciliation%20efforts%20that%20took%20place%20after%20George%20Floyd's%20murder%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Minneapolis%20police%2C%20many%20white%20residents%20of%20Jasper%20sought%20to%20assuage%20their%20Black%20neighbors%20that%20they%20would%20come%20together%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20horrific%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnation%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fjames-byrd-murder-jasper-texas%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20Washington%20Post%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20describes%20a%20town%20that%20in%20many%20ways%20has%20sought%20to%20move%20forward%20while%20downplaying%20a%20crime%20that%20for%2025%20years%20has%20defined%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20reported%20that%20Byrd%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20local%20school%20district's%20textbooks%20on%20history%20in%20the%20Lone%20Star%20State.%20The%20crime%20perpetuated%20upon%20Byrd%20is%20also%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Jasper%20County%20Historical%20Museum%2C%20which%20has%20been%20open%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Byrd's%20family%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20local%20officials%20haven't%20offered%20much%20support%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20keep%20Byrd's%20name%20alive%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELouvon%20Byrd%20Harris%2C%20Byrd's%20younger%20sister%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20many%20people%20simply%20%26quot%3Bwant%20to%20forget%20what%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20know%20who%20people%20really%20are%20once%20the%20cameras%20are%20gone.%20And%20once%20the%20cameras%20were%20gone%2C%20people%20started%20saying%2C%20'Poor%20Jasper%2C%20we're%20victims%2C%20too%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Shultz%2C%20one%20of%20the%20two%20white%20members%20on%20the%20Jasper%20City%20Council%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20residents%20continue%20to%20bear%20the%20burden%20%E2%80%94%20unfairly%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20horrific%20crime.%20(Two%20of%20the%20men%20who%20killed%20Byrd%20have%20already%20been%20executed%20by%20the%20state%2C%20while%20the%20third%20man%20is%20serving%20a%20life%20sentence%20and%20is%20up%20for%20parole%20in%202038.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20what%20happened%20was%20the%20people%20in%20Jasper's%20fault.%20I%20think%20people%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20judge%20Jasper%20on%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20past%2C%20not%20the%20city%20that%20Jasper%20is%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAnd%20Jasper%20Mayor%20Anderson%20Land%2C%20who%20is%20Black%20and%20knew%20Byrd%20growing%20up%2C%20even%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20city%20needed%20a%20fresh%20perception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20family's%20job%20to%20keep%20James's%20memory%20alive%20and%20I'm%20here%20to%20support%20them%20in%20that.%20But%20in%20order%20for%20Jasper%20to%20grow%2C%20we%20must%20move%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jasper%2C%20Texas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ea5171b413420019a41181%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20section%20of%20Huff%20Creek%20Road%20in%20Jasper%2C%20Texas%2C%20where%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%2C%20was%20dragged%20to%20his%20death.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJuan%20Lozano%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EMany%20Black%20residents%20believe%20otherwise%2C%20though%2C%20as%20they%20have%20not%20healed%20from%20the%20brutal%20hate%20crime%20and%20point%20to%20deep%20inequities%20that%20still%20exist%20in%20the%20area%2C%20which%20include%20sharp%20income%20divides%20between%20Black%20and%20white%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20much%20has%20changed%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20retired%20nursing%20aide%20Betty%20Lane%20told%20The%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EWhile%20Byrd's%20murder%20prompted%20the%20Texas%20legislature's%202001%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2001%2F05%2F12%2Fus%2Fgovernor-of-texas-signs-a-hate-crimes-bill.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20Hate%20Crimes%20Act%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcrt%2Fmatthew-shepard-and-james-byrd-jr-hate-crimes-prevention-act-2009-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealong%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Matthew%20Shepard%20and%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20Hate%20Crimes%20Prevention%20Act%2C%20which%20passed%20by%20Congress%20was%20signed%20into%20law%20in%202009%2C%20his%20family%20has%20still%20sought%20to%20do%20more%20to%20keep%20his%20legacy%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20murder%2C%20the%20family%20launched%20the%20Byrd%20Foundation%20for%20Racial%20Healing.%20And%20they%20sought%20to%20open%20a%20museum%20that%20would%20be%20focused%20on%20racial%20reconciliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EBut%20a%20l