20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20base%20attendance%20data%20of%20the%20initial%201%2C543%20beneficiary%20schools%20was%20compared%20against%20that%20of%20neighbouring%20schools%20within%201-2%20km%20by%20considering%20the%20geographical%20coordinates%20of%20the%20schools%2C%20reported%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffree-breakfast-scheme-has-improved-attendance-in-schools-tamil-nadu-govt-study-1200572.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20considered%20only%20schools%20with%20enrolment%20of%2025%20and%20above%20and%20schools%20with%20consistent%20attendance%20reporting%20above%2075%25.%20This%20left%20the%20study%20with%2072%20beneficiary%20schools%20each%20mapped%20with%20at%20least%20two%20to%2015%20neighbouring%20schools%2C%20which%20took%20the%20total%20to%20414.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuick%20rewind%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20many%20pioneering%20schemes%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20providing%20food%20to%20the%20school%20children%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20an%20initiative%20that%20improved%20the%20attendance%20and%20reduced%20malnutrition%20among%20socially%20struggling%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1920%3A%20The%20then%20Mayor%20of%20Chennai%20Corporation%2C%20Sir%20PT%20Thiyagarayar%2C%20passed%20a%20resolution%20to%20implement%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20in%20Corporation%20School%20at%20Thousand%20Lights%2C%20Chennai.%20The%20scheme%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20school%E2%80%99s%20student%20strength.%20The%20scheme%20was%20expanded%20to%20a%20few%20more%20schools%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1947%3A%20Due%20to%20financial%20constraints%2C%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20was%20abandoned%2C%20except%20in%20Harijan%20Welfare%20Department-run%20schools.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1957%3A%20Chief%20minister%20K%20Kamaraj%20resumed%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20for%20primary%20school%20students.%20%E2%82%B910%20lakh%20was%20allotted%20for%20implementing%20this%20scheme%2C%20with%20a%20clause%20that%20it%20should%20not%20exceeding%20%E2%82%B918%20per%20child%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1982%3A%20Chief%20minister%20MG%20Ramachandran%20introduced%20the%20Nutritious%20Meal%20Programme.%20Children%20in%20pre-school%20and%20primary%20schools%20were%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1989%3A%C2%A0%20Chief%20minister%20M%20Karunanidhi%20included%20an%20egg%20every%20two%20weeks%20to%20the%20menu%20of%20the%20nutritious%20meal%20scheme.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1998-2008%3A%20The%20egg%20count%20gradually%20increased%20from%20one%20per%20week%20to%20three%20per%20week.%20The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20provided%20bananas%20for%20the%20children%20who%20would%20not%20eat%20eggs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2010%3A%20Egg%20count%20goes%20to%20five%20every%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Ftamilnadu%2Ftn-extends-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools-brings-cheer-to-17-lakh-primary-students%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20South%20First.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693036826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121001%2FBreakfast-scheme-in-Chennai-2-750x500-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Chief%20Minister's%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20provides%20breakfast%20to%20primary%20school%20children%2C%20addressing%20hunger%20and%20improving%20attendance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2